{
    "name": "Beggar",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Beggar",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Wherever there is poverty, there are beggars. Beggars are truly the downtrodden of society, as folks who have been cast out into the streets due to a variety of setbacks or the weight of circumstance. Some beggars work for underworld organizations as lookouts, spies, or even hired muscle on the cheap\u2014sometimes by choice, but often not.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "NPC Core",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "NPC Core pg. 40",
                        "alt": "NPC Core pg. 40",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 236
                    },
                    "page": 40
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Downtrodden",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Braving The Mob",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "A mob is a violent crowd that works as greater difficult terrain and hazardous terrain, dealing 1d4 damage for each square entered. A creature can spend a single action to attempt a DC 16 Intimidation check, clearing the mob from all squares adjacent to them on a success (or all squares within 10 feet on a critical success). This action has the concentrate, emotion, manipulate, and mental traits. If the mob is meant to be a combat encounter, you can instead use the deluded mob.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "NPC Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "NPC Core pg. 40",
                                "alt": "NPC Core pg. 40",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 236
                            },
                            "page": 40
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
